<p>Basically, what my program is intended to do, is to output input's each character's ascii code in binary. However, whatever I type in I get 1111111, and it is bugging me out, because I have no clue what could cause the problem   Here is the code:</p>  <pre><code>.model small .stack 200h  .data buferis  db 16 dup("z")  .code pr1:  mov ax, @data mov ds, ax   mov dx, offset buferis mov ah, 0Ah int 21h    mov bx, 02h mov cl, buferis+01h    mov ah, 02h mov dl, 10 int 21h   ciklas:     mov al, [buferis+bx]     mov ch, 7      vidinis_ciklas:         mov dl, '0'         shl al, 1         cmp al, 10000000b         jl toliau         mov dl, '1'         toliau:         int 21h         dec ch         cmp ch, 0         jne vidinis_ciklas      mov dl, ' '     int 21h     inc bx  loop ciklas   mov ah, 4ch mov al, 00h int 21h  end pr1 </code></pre>